The paper discusses the optimization of Capsule Networks, which are primarily used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on improving the training time of CapsNets, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel learning rate policy and weight sharing technique, which are both related to the optimization of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of CapsNets in various machine learning tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, such as word embeddings, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
